post_text: If you are wanting your child(ren) to return for in-person instruction for the 2nd six weeks the deadline for notification is Monday, Sept.14th. Please send an email to Kelly.bray@bosquevilleisd.org and I will make sure we get them on our in-person list. If you have any questions feel free to email or call me. I will resend a copy of the Campus Operational Plan to you so you can review everything before your child returns. Currently, we have had no COVID cases at the elementary and only one in the district. We have had some strep going around and lots of allergies. The students continue to do an incredible job at following our new normal. I look forward to seeing those students who have already let me know they will be returning the 2nd six weeks.

post_text: WOW!!! Today was the staff‚Äôs first day back and it was so good to all be together. I missed them. Let me tell you how blessed your kids are with having all these great people to love on them each day. Today, I had to share our new ‚Äúnormal‚Äù while looking out into a roomful of masked faces. The positive attitudes and ideas that I could hear from those sharing some great ideas just made me smile. (I hope they could see that behind my mask!) I know the decision to keep your kids at home or to send them in person is a hard one but the good news is either decision will be the right one because you are doing what your family needs to do. Either way, we will be ready to give your kids the best possible year! I will be sharing a more specific plan next week on what your child‚Äôs day will look like and you will also be hearing from the teachers. Our theme this year is ‚ÄúCELEBRATION‚Äù and we can‚Äôt wait to celebrate the start of a new school year! üíô Go Bulldogs!

This is an updated message for Bosqueville ISD parents regarding the 20-21 school year. As most of you know on Tuesday, July 21st the McLennan County Health Department closed schools in our County to in-person instruction until Tuesday, September 8, 2020. BISD will begin Remote (Asynchronous) Instruction on our regularly scheduled start date of Thursday, August 13, 2020, for all students. You will be receiving an email or you can check the school website for detailed information.

As most of you know on Tuesday, July 21st the McLennan County Health Department closed schools in our County to in-person instruction until Tuesday, September 8, 2020. BISD will begin Remote (Asynchronous) Instruction on our regularly scheduled start date of Thursday, August 13, 2020, for all students. You will be receiving an email or you can check the school website for detailed information.

We are planning a parade for next Friday, April 24 at 2:00. I will send out the route and more information on Monday. We miss your children so much and I‚Äôm heartbroken from today‚Äôs news. Please hug your kids and let them know that we will do something with all of them once all of this has cleared.

The Bulldog Back Porch
April 13 at 12:50 PM ¬∑

Good afternoon,
I have created a Facebook page, Instagram account and a YouTube Channel for The Bulldog Back Porch. I was truly blessed have some of the greatest/humble musicians to perform on my stage for my 4th grade class this year. Everyone was so great with the students and had so much patience answering all of their questions. My students have all become lifelong fans of these artist. My goal is keep this amazing talent coming in (once we get back to school.) This week I will be releasing one artist every day for the next seven days. Also, I want to thank everyone involved in making this happen. Bosqueville Elementary Faculty and Staff are the best. McNamara Home Solutions, LLC Trevor Lamb Travis Veselka Kolby CooperCory MorrowKoe WetzelThe Powell Brothers Mike RyanHuser Brother BandJD Casper Gabriel Muniz Photography Colin Zamarippa

post_text: As most of you are aware we will not be able to go back to our building for school until May 4th. My heart is breaking for everyone but we will continue to work towards providing instruction as best as we all can. I have sent out some things for the teachers to give me feedback on and we will work on our plan as we go forward these next few weeks. We will be in contact with each of you soon. The district will be sending out more information later this afternoon. Give your kids a hug and let them know we miss them terribly. Please let us know if we can be of any help during these upcoming weeks.

Parents:
Definitely not the way we wanted to end our spring break but we will get through this. I will send out information as I get it and keep you as updated as possible. On Tuesday we will begin providing pick up meals for students. Be looking for more information tomorrow on how this will work. I will also provide information on how we will go forward with continuing instruction when we know more of a timeline on school closures.

You already know our staff is great and they have been incredible with offering to come up and help with whatever is needed to be done. If you have a need, please don‚Äôt hesitate to contact me at Kelly.bray@bosquevilleisd.org or your child‚Äôs home room teacher and we will do what we can or help provide you with resources.

Check back daily for updates and we all hope to be back to our regular routines soon.

Kelly Bray

post_text:
After the recent update to Parent Portal, we had several reports of alerts not being sent from Ascender ParentPortal. We notified the Service Center and they investigated the issue and rebooted the system. Unfortunately when this rebooted, if parents had any unread alerts, new alerts were launched. In this case, any unread alerts caused a notification that today your student was absent or tardy when it could have been an earlier date. Please review the attendance calendar for your student if you are needing more information.

We apologize for the inconvenience, but we are glad the system is operational from this point forward and we hope you are liking the new design.

Mrs. Bray

Bosqueville FFA
November 4, 2019 at 4:36 PM ¬∑

Today was a great day for Bosqueville FFA, we competed at the Heart of Texas District contest. We have several teams advancing to Area on November 23rd.
The top 3 teams received banners and top 2 will move on to Area.

Ag Advocacy placed 2nd, members were Emma Robertson, Hadleigh Gillett, Regan Roscher and Dalton Light.

Niki Clark placed 1st in Jr. Creed.

Daniel Roe placed 2nd in Job Interview.

Chapter Quiz tied for 2nd but lost the tie breaker and were 3rd, members were Emma Robertson, Daniel Roe, Adrian Amaro, and Maci Smelscer.

Greenhand Chapter Conducting placed 3rd, members were Justin Moore, Abigail Sanders, Savannah Garrett, Morgan Frost, Morgan Beauchamp, Sadie Bawduniak, Logan Hill, Hannah Heath, Kaley King,

Greenhand quiz placed 12th, members were Karley Willenborg, Morgan Beauchamp, Morgan Frost, and Niki Clark.

Radio Broadcasting placed 8th out of 15 teams, members were Berkley Cowan, Karley Karley Willenborg, and Nash Shaw.

Sophie Bawduniak placed 7th out of 17 in Sr. Creed!

All of these kids did an amazing job and we are so proud of everyone of them!!
